Citations
Date:  21/4/1952
Source:  Letter
Author:  PETER NEWTON
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  `Roll the knot means to roll one's swag - musterers on the bigger places shift camp as the muster progresses and as their `gear' consists of blankets and a change of clothes, this is rolled into a ...bundle for loading onto the packhorse whenever they shift camp.
